on technology. Charles worked for Esurance in 2006 and 2007, then rejoined the company in 2012. He has also worked at LeBoeuf, Lamb, Greene & MacRae for 8 years and Nixon Peabody for 5 years.         Grace Lee Vice President of Human Resources See bio [+] Hide bio [–]         Ravi Narayan Managing Director, Head of Product Engineering, & Chief Information Officer See bio [+] Hide bio [–]         Mark Pitchford Managing Director & Chief Sales and Marketing Officer See bio [+] Hide bio [–]         Mark Simmonds Managing Director, Product See bio [+] Hide bio [–]        Grace joined Esurance in 2016 after a 26-year career with Allstate. Her broad business experience at Allstate spans leadership roles in claims, sales operations, and human resources. Grace's background in HR includes supporting various departments as a business partner, driving talent strategies, recruiting, and leadership development. Grace earned her BA in Psychology from Boston College, and has her Professional in Human Resources (PHR®) certification, as well as a property and casualty license.   Ravi brings nearly three decades of technology and leadership experience to his role at Esurance. Before joining the team in 2016, he held a variety of technology and product development roles with eBay and PayPal, and served as director of software development at Amazon.   Mark has more than 25 years of experience in marketing, product management, and customer care. Prior to joining Esurance in 2012, Mark served for 4 years as Allstate's senior vice president of direct sales and service. Previous experience includes executive positions in several telecommunications firms, including Hanaro Telecom, Qwest Communications, and AT&T.   Mark brings 20 years of insurance industry experience to his role as managing director and chief product officer. Following successful senior leadership roles with Liberty Mutual and CSAA Insurance Group, among others, Mark joined the team at Esurance in 2016. An alum of Dartmouth College, he brings a diversity of expertise in many areas, including product, underwriting, finance, operations, and more.           our associates      Through our Meet Esurance series, we invite you to get to know the fresh-thinking, problem-solving people who make Esurance just plain better.              Katie F.      sales trainer          Erika V.      sales support lead          Derek M.      licensed customer service rep   Check out more Meet Esurance videos:    Check out more Meet Esurance videos: [+]             Nandini E. director, systems engineering  [+]            Erin H. customer service rep  [+]            Casey S. claims network manager  [+]             Katie F., sales and service trainer Office: Tampa, Florida Started with Esurance: October 2011 What Katie does each day: Takes new sales associates through a 7-week training course to help make them the knowledgeable insurance experts our customers have come to expect How her colleagues describe her: Quiet leader, outgoing, energetic, knowledgeable, people person, busy bee What she loves about Esurance: The encouragement to be your best and the ability to have a life outside of work      Erika V., sales support lead Office: Tampa, Florida Started with Esurance: May 2011 How she started her career: By googling "Esurance" What she's known for: In-depth insurance knowledge, drive, and some serious bling Most passionate about: Insurance and figure skating (of course!) Proudest moment: Earning her well-deserved promotion, because her new role fits her to a tee      Derek M., licensed customer service rep Office: Sioux Falls, South Dakota ("Where the magic happens.") Started with Esurance: June 2010 Favorite quote: "Sometimes it's best to see what you can do instead of focusing on what cannot be done." What his boss says: "Derek influences others to want to be better." Celebrity look-alike: Ben Affleck His car's name: Irene      Nandini E., director of systems engineering Office: San Francisco, Californ