United of Omaha – Get A Life Insurance Policy





















Apply for Whole Life Insurance
Need Help? Call (800) 995-6236







Frequently Asked Questions
Q: What is life insurance?

							A: Life insurance is a policy that provides financial assistance to a beneficiary after the insured person passes away. There are several different life insurance products on the market such as whole life insurance and term life insurance. 
			            
Q: What do I need to decide before buying a policy?

			            	A: You should determine two factors before buying a new term life insurance policy: the coverage amount, and the policy beneficiary.
			            
Q: How much life insurance do I need?

			            	A: The necessary amount of life insurance coverage varies depending on the needs of you and your dependents. Our licensed insurance agents** can help you find a policy to fit your individual needs.
			            
Q: What is a beneficiary?

			            	A: A beneficiary is the person, trust, charity, or estate who receives the policy benefit after the insured person passes away. The insured person will designate a beneficiary during the enrollment process.
			            
 Q: Do I need a medical exam to qualify?

			            	A: You do not need a medical exam to qualify for a United of Omaha Life Insurance Company (United of Omaha) Whole Life Guaranteed policy.
			            
Q: Can the insurance company terminate my life insurance policy?

			            	A: The insurance company cannot cancel your policy as long as the premiums are paid. In addition, the policy cannot be canceled due to any health changes.
			            
Q: Does the policy pay out in the case of suicide?

			            	A: A suicide, while sane or insane, is not covered by the policy for the first two years (except in North Dakota which has a time cap of one year). If the policy owner’s death is ruled a suicide during this time window, United of Omaha will refund all of the premiums paid. 
			            
Q: How much life insurance coverage is available?

			            	A: United of Omaha offers death benefits amounts ranging from $3,000 - $25,000 for the Whole Life Guaranteed policy.
			            
Q: Will my premiums increase in the future?

			            	A: Your insurance premiums will not increase in the future. Whole Life Guaranteed premiums do not increase as you age or if your health changes. 
			            






